HEADWORD: Lophine
<hw>Loph"ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a tuft or
crest of feathers.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A nitrogenous organic
base obtained by the oxidation of amarine, and regarded as a derivative
of benzoic aldehyde. It is obtained in long white crystalline tufts, --
whence its name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

